#EXTM3U
# /srv/badabing/playlists/badabing-starter-playlist.m3u
#
# The "Bada Bing" classical starter playlist — well-known, crowd-pleasing pieces
# whose COMPOSITIONS are firmly public domain. (Remember: the RECORDING must also
# be free — use the Musopen/archive.org CC0 sets from fetch-music.sh, or your own
# files. The paths below are RELATIVE to MPD's music_directory; they will resolve
# once you have downloaded/dropped recordings of these pieces with sensible
# folder names. Adjust the paths to match your actual files, then:
#     mpc load badabing-starter-playlist
#     mpc play
# Or skip the playlist entirely and just let continuous-shuffle play the whole
# library — badabing-mpd-init.sh does that by default.)
#
# This file doubles as a curation guide: even if your filenames differ, it tells
# you WHICH pieces make a tasteful, recognizable rotation for a relaxed outdoor
# (chicken-approved) atmosphere — nothing too bombastic or sleep-disrupting.
#
# ---- The dozen ----
#EXTINF:-1,Johann Pachelbel — Canon in D major
Pachelbel/Canon_in_D.flac
#EXTINF:-1,Antonio Vivaldi — The Four Seasons, "Spring" (La primavera), I. Allegro
Vivaldi/Four_Seasons_Spring_1_Allegro.flac
#EXTINF:-1,Johann Sebastian Bach — Air on the G String (Orchestral Suite No. 3)
Bach/Air_on_the_G_String.flac
#EXTINF:-1,Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart — Eine kleine Nachtmusik, I. Allegro
Mozart/Eine_kleine_Nachtmusik_1_Allegro.flac
#EXTINF:-1,Claude Debussy — Clair de lune (Suite bergamasque)
Debussy/Clair_de_Lune.flac
#EXTINF:-1,Erik Satie — Gymnopédie No. 1
Satie/Gymnopedie_No_1.flac
#EXTINF:-1,Frédéric Chopin — Nocturne in E-flat major, Op. 9 No. 2
Chopin/Nocturne_Op9_No2.flac
#EXTINF:-1,Ludwig van Beethoven — Symphony No. 7 in A, II. Allegretto
Beethoven/Symphony_7_2_Allegretto.flac
#EXTINF:-1,Edvard Grieg — Peer Gynt Suite No. 1, "Morning Mood"
Grieg/Peer_Gynt_Morning_Mood.flac
#EXTINF:-1,Camille Saint-Saëns — The Carnival of the Animals, "The Swan" (Le cygne)
Saint-Saens/The_Swan.flac
#EXTINF:-1,Gabriel Fauré — Pavane, Op. 50
Faure/Pavane_Op50.flac
#EXTINF:-1,Edward Elgar — Salut d'Amour, Op. 12
Elgar/Salut_dAmour.flac
